The national executive of Brazil'smost militant trade union group has proposed a general strikefor July 15 in protest at the government's austerity program.    A spokeswoman for the Workers' Confederation (CUT) toldReuters the proposal would be discussed within the trade unionmovement. On Friday the government of President Jose Sarneyintroduced austerity measures to try to combat the country'shigh inflation rate, currently running at more than 1,000 pct ayear.    It scrapped a trigger mechanism which had guaranteedregular pay rises in line with high inflation.    Trade unions say real wages are dropping by about a third. Reuter&#3;